metadata.name: VOODOOZ #307
metadata.description:
Need some luck, happiness, and lucky charm? Alexis Bacci’s VOODOOZ are here for you! Will you dare to mint and to collect?

VOODOOZ is a collection of 512 magical dolls of 3 types: basic, collector and boss - with or without accessories; a tribute to Voodoo culture entirely hand drawn by the comics author Alexis Bacci.

Each VOODOOZ doll has specific and unique magical powers, bringing luck and happiness, a lucky charm in your journey in the NFTs world!

Voodooz come with optional accessories: the SNAKE, the POTION and the RING.

• The SNAKE can complete the inner circle of life and vital energy
• The POTION will help the doll to spell, protect and increase its skills
• The RING gives more power and can be used as a talisman
• The HOLY TRINITY gathers the 3 accessories above

Tip: try to grab a SNAKE + a POTION + a RING and a special VOODOOZ NFT will be airdropped to your wallet for free.

Alexis Bacci is a comics book author who has been working in the cartoon and movie industry for two decades. In 2021 he minted his 1st NFTs on ETH, the Tengu Diaries, and his Girlz series on Tezos.

VOODOOZ are Alexis’ genesis series on fx(hash), pay attention!

metadata.name: NESTED IDENTITIES #130
metadata.description:
Nested identities redact fingerprints but deeper meaning can still be found.

Nested identifies refers to the idea that a person may have multiple identities that are interconnected and interdependent. These identities may be related to a person's cultural background, ethnicity, nationality, gender, sexual orientation, social class, profession, and other factors. It is possible that a person may want to conceal or redact certain aspects of their identity in order to protect their privacy or to avoid discrimination or persecution. However, even if certain details about a person's identity are hidden or redacted, it may still be possible to infer deeper meaning or understand more about their experiences and perspectives based on the context in which they express themselves and the information that is available.


The concept of nested identities highlights the complexity and multifaceted nature of a person's identity, and how different aspects of identity can intersect and influence each other. It is important to recognize and respect the diversity of identities that people may hold, and to be mindful of the ways in which power dynamics and social context can shape how people present and express their identities. It is also important to recognize that people's identities may evolve and change over time, and that everyone has the right to self-identify and to define their own identity on their own terms.

Press p to download a high quality export.

metadata.name: La Invernada #78
metadata.description:
This project is about my mother's lifestyle. Her work is breeding and herding goats, cows and horses.
She lives a cyclical life marked by two major stages during her livestock year: "La Veranada" and "La Invernada". My last work was about "La Veranada", this work is about "La Invernada", I hope you enjoy it.
Time in the life of a criancero is cyclical. Everything comes and goes, and comes back and comes back. Nature, so present, so in connection with the man and woman who inhabit it, marks the times perhaps like no other place.
 The succession of the seasons, the weather, the buds and "La Invernada", the sowing, the pastures, the harvest and the snows.
"La Invernada" is the place during what we could call the long winter, that is, from April to November.
"La Invernada" is down in the plains, in the pampas, in accessible places, where it is easy to supply forage to the goats that calve between October and November.
The "Criancero" rides a horse every day and, accompanied by his dogs, goes to "watch" the goats. They distinguish them in the distance. Every day is the same and different at the same time. Caring for, watching over and keeping the goats healthy and safe.
"El puesto" is their home. In the stall they use the water from the river, which they draw with a water pump, for their hygiene. Water for consumption is brought in jerry cans from "Vertientes", located about 10 km away.
 The hens roam freely throughout the day, when night comes some go to sleep in the "gallinero" and others simply sleep on small plants.
As you can see, life here is simple, solitary and with a lot of work.
I want to thank all those who have taken the trouble to read the story. I hope you liked it.
You can find real photos and videos of "La Invernada" on my twitter profile.

Features:
10 Color Palettes.
10 types of Animal pen.
Various types of chickens.
14 types of herbs.
10 types of flowerpot.
4 types of trees.
7 types of rivers.
The barn has 4 sizes.
The moon has a very varied range of x and y positions.
6% chance of getting snowy weather in the piece.


Press "S" in live mode to save the 2600 x 3000 image.
Note that the algorithm may take some time to run.
Created by Fernando. NFT 2.0 license.

metadata.name: Spring will be back again  #87
metadata.description:
This project aims to capture the essence of the Japanese hanami experience where people gather to admire the fleeting beauty of the cherry blossom.

It's a representation of the beauty of an unreal nature where the details of the leaves and flowers are imaginary and always different.

While some trees in the animation are depicted in full bloom with delicate petals and lush leaves, other may yet have to blossom or may already have lost their blooms, or even don't have leaves or flowers at all.

Crafted entirely with lines of code in vanilla javascript, without the use of reference images or templates.

There are over 20 distinct features that define each token and the animation is also interactive

Each time the animation is played, it generates a unique and dynamic display of the blossom trees, while still maintaining the features defined by the underlying token.

You may also change the resolution or the layout at any time, or toggle the animation mode.



Commands

[1] Low resolution
[2] Normal resolution
[3] High res
[4] Super high res
[5] Print res (not animated)

[a] or [space] Reload in animation mode
[s] Reload in static mode
[d] Download snapshot in current resolution

Change layout:

[z] 1x2.5 (Portrait)
[x] 1x2
[c] 1x1.5 (default in mobile)
[v] 1x1 Square
[b] 1.5x1 (Landscape, default in desktop)
[n] 2x1
[m] 2.5x1

May be unresponsive on higher resolutions (in those cases turning off the animation mode is recommended)

metadata.name: I AM UNFOLDING #147
metadata.description:
In the past, I was but fragments
Rough and jagged
Indefinitely, I weathered and grew
A sculpture formed, unstructured

In the present, I am the precipice
A grandiose monolith
My angles sharp, my lines precise
A work of art, restructured

The future looms before
A blank formlessness yet to be
My function undefined
In perpetuity, unfolding

-----------------------------------------

Best efforts have been made to optimize this project; however, for best performance, a machine with a dedicated GPU is recommended. Viewing the project in live mode is also recommended.

S - export a high resolution image.
P - pause the animation.

metadata.name: BLOCK PARTY #241
metadata.description:
A generative algorithm exploring isometric grids and recursive divisions with an emphasis on contrasting colors.

A random rectange division is so simple yet creates vastly different and interesting outputs.

An isometric grid provides a unique perspective to the recursion giving each piece a certain depth and contrast.

When does chaotic randomness become beauty and what interesting patterns may emerge?

Press 's' in live mode to save image. Best viewed after save.

* Original code by Matt Lehoullier with p5.js

metadata.name: Millefoglie #435
metadata.description:
"A mille-feuille (French pronunciation: ​[mil fœj], "thousand-sheets"), also known by the names Napoleon, vanilla slice, and custard slice, is a dessert made of puff pastry layered with pastry cream. Its modern form was influenced by improvements made by Marie-Antoine Carême.

Traditionally, a mille-feuille is made up of three layers of puff pastry (pâte feuilletée), alternating with two layers of pastry cream (crème pâtissière). The top pastry layer is finished in various ways: sometimes it is topped with whipped cream, or it may be dusted with icing sugar, cocoa, pastry crumbs, or sliced almonds. It may also be glazed with icing or fondant alone, or in alternating white (icing) and brown (chocolate) or other colored icing stripes, and combed to create a marbled effect." — Wikipedia

Prints available upon request: prints@stefancontiero.com
Best enjoyed on browsers supporting Display-P3 color gamut.

License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

@stefan_contiero

metadata.name: ⚖ Justice #42
metadata.description:
This work is one of the Nfts that belong to the collection "⚖ Justice"

Technique: Multi-layered generative art processed with Photoshop
Size: 3000 × 2000 px

These generative artworks are conceived with the intention of conveying a social message of denouncing violence and suffering, rebelling against injustices, and defending human rights. Each piece expresses a strong sense of social commitment that goes beyond words and manifests itself through art.

Each work invites reflection on the current state of our society. Justice should be a universal right for every individual, but too often it becomes a matter of money and power.
These artworks speak to the viewer on a visceral level, inviting them to contemplate the injustices in our world and to take action.

metadata.name: Chaos #1019
metadata.description:
Chaos seems to be the only constant thing in the universe. No matter the age, situation, location, success of any individual, from time to time, each one of us undergoes bouts of uncertainty. Chaos is something that is often portrayed in a negative light, but every once in a while it can end up being something beautiful as well. For example a nice surprise in an otherwise hectic day! 

This generative token is a celebration of chaos, a ray of hope amidst the tumultuous times that we live in, an escape from our internal vulnerabilities, a sense of closure and acceptance even when a lot might be going on in our lives. 

Feel free to mint as many as you want, gift it to your friends or loved ones, sell it, resell it or even make derivatives of your particular mint. I put in a reserve list for everybody who has collected any of my NFTs in the past so that my supporters don't miss out! This token is an expression of my gratitude to my supporters, and the entire FxHash community. Thank you all! 
Keep making art. No matter how hard today might be, be hopeful for a better tomorrow. 

Made with love in cables.gl
